messages.message:
Patch Set 9:

After carefully re-reading my patch (Patch set 8) I realised I had overlooked a few things:
 - requests in an hal must share the same archive_id;
 - removing an hai from an hal does not ensure that there is enough space for a different hai (their size might differ);
 - I did not try hard enough to find an hal that could hold the RESTORE request I was trying to schedule.

This should be fixed now.
